ementation of the ceasefire but repeatedly delayed them . . The talks never took place. The lesson for Hamas was clear. Even if an agreement was brokered by the US and Egypt, Israel could still fail to honour it.'&lt;/ref>&lt;ref>Adam Withnall,  [https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/israel-gaza-conflict-israel-breaks-ceasefire-in-minutes-as-eight-year-old-girl-killed-in-air-strike-9645558.html  'Israel-Gaza conflict: Israel 'breaks ceasefire in minutes' as eight-year-old girl killed in air strike,'] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180621221209/https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/israel-gaza-conflict-israel-breaks-ceasefire-in-minutes-as-eight-year-old-girl-killed-in-air-strike-9645558.html |date=21 June 2018 }} [[The Independent]] I4 August 2014&lt;/ref>&lt;ref>[[Yousef Munayyer]], [http://www.thejerusalemfund.org/8747/israelgaza-cease-fire-dynamics-breakdown  'Israel/Gaza Cease-Fire Dynamics Breakdown,'] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180621194348/http://www.thejerusalemfund.org/8747/israelgaza-cease-fire-dynamics-breakdown |date=21 June 2018 }}  [[The Jerusalem Fund]] 2014&lt;/ref> PA President [[Mahmoud Abbas]] has expressed his approval of the Egyptian border restrictions. In 2014 and subsequent years, Abbas supported Egypt's crackdown on [[Gaza Strip smuggling tunnels|smuggling tunnels]], and welcomed the flooding of the tunnels by Egypt in coordination with the PA.&lt;ref name=aljazeera1214/>

